#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:5
msgid "Spline IK"
msgstr "Spline IK 样条IK"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:7
msgid ""
"Spline IK is a constraint which aligns a chain of bones along a curve. By leveraging the ease and flexibility of achieving aesthetically pleasing shapes offered by curves and "
"the predictability and well integrated control offered by bones, Spline IK is an invaluable tool in the riggers' toolbox. It is particularly well suited for rigging flexible "
"body parts such as tails, tentacles, and spines, as well as inorganic items such as ropes."
msgstr ""
"样条线IK是约束一条骨骼链沿曲线对齐。通过利用曲线的易用性和灵活性实现了美观形状和为骨骼提供可预测性以及良好的综合控制，样条线IK是绑定工具箱中非常宝贵的工具。它特别适用于绑定柔软"
"的身体部位，如尾巴，触手和脊椎，以及无机物品如绳索。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:14
msgid "Full description of the settings for the spline IK are detailed on the :doc:`Spline IK </rigging/constraints/tracking/spline_ik>` page."
msgstr "对样条IK的设置充分说明在详细的文档 :doc:`Spline IK </rigging/constraints/tracking/spline_ik>` page 页。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:19
msgid "Basic Setup"
msgstr "Basic Setup 基本设置"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:21
msgid ""
"The Spline IK Constraint is not strictly an 'Inverse Kinematics' method (i.e. IK Constraint), but rather a 'Forward Kinematics' method (i.e. normal bone posing). However, it "
"still shares some characteristics of the IK Constraint, such as operating on multiple bones not being usable for Objects, and being evaluated after all other constraints have "
"been evaluated. It should be noted that if a Standard IK chain and a Spline IK chain both affect a bone at the same time the Standard IK chain takes priority. Such setups are "
"best avoided though, since the results may be difficult to control."
msgstr ""
"样条IK约束不是严格的“反向运动学”方法（即IK约束），而是一种“正向运动学”的方法（即正常的骨骼摆姿势）。然而，它仍然具有IK约束的一些特性，如对多个不适用于物体的骨骼操作，以及在所有"
"其他约束被计算之后进行计算。需要注意的是，如果标准的IK链和样条IK链同时影响一根骨头，标准的IK链优先。不过，最好避免这种设置，因为结果可能很难控制。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:30
msgid "To setup Spline IK, it is necessary to have a chain of connected bones and a curve to constrain these bones to:"
msgstr "建立样条IK，它必须有一个连接的骨骼链和曲线来约束这些骨骼:"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:33
msgid ""
"With the last bone in the chain selected, add a :doc:`Spline IK </rigging/constraints/tracking/spline_ik>` Constraint from the Bone Constraints tab in the Properties Editor."
msgstr "选择链中最后一根骨头，从属性编辑器的骨骼约束标签添加 :doc:`Spline IK </rigging/constraints/tracking/spline_ik>` 约束。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:36
msgid "Set the 'Chain Length' setting to the number of bones in the chain (starting from and including the selected bone) that should be influenced by the curve."
msgstr "设置 'Chain Length（链长）' 设置链的骨骼应受到曲线的影响数量（从包括选择的骨骼和开始骨骼）。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:38
msgid "Finally, set the 'Target' field to the curve that should control the curve."
msgstr "最后，将“目标”字段设置为应该控制的曲线。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:40
msgid "Congratulations, the bone chain is now controlled by the curve."
msgstr "恭喜，骨骼链现在由曲线控制。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:44
msgid "Settings and Controls"
msgstr "Settings and Controls 设置和控制"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:47
msgid "Roll Control"
msgstr "Roll Control 扭转控制"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:49
msgid ""
"To control the 'twist' or 'roll' of the Spline IK chain, the standard methods of rotating the bones in the chain along their y-axes still apply. For example, simply rotate the "
"bones in the chain around their y-axes to adjust the roll of the chain from that point onwards. Applying copy rotation constraints on the bones should also work."
msgstr "控制样条IK链的“扭曲(twist)”或“(滚动roll)”，仍然适用的标准方法沿Y轴的链中旋转骨骼链。例如，只需旋转骨骼在Y轴链调整的链滚动从那时起。在骨骼上应用复制旋转约束也应该会工作。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:57
msgid "Offset Controls"
msgstr "Offset Controls 偏移量控制"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:59
msgid ""
"The entire bone chain can be made to follow the shape of the curve while still being able to be placed at an arbitrary point in 3D-space when the 'Chain Offset' option is "
"enabled. By default, this option is not enabled, and the bones will be made to follow the curve in its untransformed position."
msgstr "整个骨骼链可以按照曲线的形状，同时当“链偏移”选项是启用时仍然可以被放置在三维空间的任意点。默认情况下，不启用此选项，和骨骼将跟随在其未变形的位置处的曲线上。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:66
msgid "Thickness Controls"
msgstr "Thickness Controls 厚度控制"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:68
msgid ""
"The thickness of the bones in the chain is controlled using the constraint's 'XZ Scale Mode' setting. This setting determines the method used for determining the scaling on "
"the X and Z axes of each bone in the chain."
msgstr "链中骨头的厚度通过使用约束的 ‘XZ缩放模式’ 设置控制的。该设置决定着用于确定每个骨头链中的 X 和 Z 轴上的缩放的方法。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:72
msgid "The available modes are:"
msgstr "可用的模式有："

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:74
msgid "None"
msgstr "None 无"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:75
msgid "this option keeps the X and Z scaling factors as 1.0."
msgstr "此选项使x和z缩放因子保持为1。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:77
msgid "Volume Preserve"
msgstr "Volume Preserve  体积保持"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:77
msgid "the X and Z scaling factors are taken as the inverse of the Y scaling factor (length of the bone), maintaining the 'volume' of the bone."
msgstr "将X和Z缩放因子视为Y缩放因子（骨的长度）的反向，保持骨骼的“体积”的。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:80
msgid "Bone Original"
msgstr "Bone Original 骨骼原点"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:80
msgid "this options just uses the X and Z scaling factors the bone would have after being evaluated in the standard way."
msgstr "这个选项只是使用骨骼标准方式计算后的X和Z缩放因子。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:82
msgid ""
"In addition to these modes, there is an option, *Use Curve Radius*. When this option is enabled, the average radius of the radii of the points on the curve where the joints of "
"each bone are placed, are used to derive X and Z scaling factors. This allows the scaling effects, determined using the modes above, to be tweaked as necessary for artistic "
"control."
msgstr ""
"除了这些模式，还有一个选项，*Use Curve Radius使用曲线半径*。当启用此选项时，将使用放置每个骨骼的关节的曲线上的点的半径的平均半径来推导X和Z缩放因子。这允许使用上述模式确定的缩放"
"效果根据艺术控制的需要进行调整。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:90
msgid "Tips for Nice Setups"
msgstr "关于好的设置提示"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:92
msgid ""
"For optimal deformations, it is recommended that the bones are roughly the same length, and that they are not too long, to facilitate a better fit to the curve. Also, bones "
"should ideally be created in a way that follows the shape of the curve in its 'rest pose' shape, to minimize the problems in areas where the curve has sharp bends which may be "
"especially noticeable when stretching is disabled."
msgstr ""
"为了最佳的变形，建议骨骼有大致相同的长度，并且它们不会太长，以便于更好地适应曲线。此外，理想情况下，骨骼应该以“重置姿势”形状的跟随曲线形状的方式创建，以最大程度地减少曲线具有尖"
"锐弯曲的区域中的问题，这在拉伸被禁用时尤其明显。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:97
msgid ""
"For control of the curve, it is recommended that hooks (in particular, Bone Hooks) are used to control the control-vertices of the curve, with one hook per control-vertex. In "
"general, only a few control-vertices should be needed for the curve (e.g. one for every 3-5 bones offers decent control)."
msgstr ""
"为了控制曲线，建议使用手柄（特别是骨骼手柄）来控制曲线的控制顶点，每个控制顶点有一个手柄。一般来说，曲线应该只需要几个控制顶点（例如，每3-5个骨骼可以提供一个合适的控制）。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:101
msgid ""
"The type of curve used does not really matter, as long as a path can be extracted from it that could also be used by the Follow Path Constraint. This really depends on the "
"level of control required from the hooks."
msgstr "所使用的曲线的类型并不重要，只要可以从中挤出也可以被跟随路径约束使用。这真的取决于手柄控制的水平。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/armatures/posing/bone_constraints/inverse_kinematics/spline_ik.rst:104
msgid ""
"When setting up the rigs, it is currently necessary to have the control bones (for controlling the curve) in a separate armature to those used for deforming the meshes (i.e. "
"the deform rig containing the Spline IK chains). This is to avoid creating pseudo \"Dependency Cycles\", since Blender's Dependency Graph can only resolve the dependencies the "
"control bones, curves, and Spline IK'ed bones on an object by object basis."
msgstr ""
"当设置绑定时，目前有必要将控制骨（用于控制曲线）与用于使网格变形的单独的骨架（即，包含样条IK链的变形绑定）分开。这是为了避免创建伪“依赖循环”，因为Blender的依赖关系图只能解析依"
"附对象上的控件骨骼，曲线和样条IK骨骼。"
